        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: guard setDeep against empty keys array in Chrome profile decoration",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where `setDeep()` with empty `keys` would create a property with empty-string key on the target object.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdd early `if (keys.length === 0) return;` guard. Production callers (`decorateOpenClawProfile`) pass non-empty literal arrays like `[\"profile\",\"info_cache\",\"Default\",\"name\"]`.\n\n## User Impact\n\nNo user-visible change. Defensive guard against edge cases.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```\nextensions/browser/src/browser/profiles.test.ts\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n     Tests  36 passed (36)\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 16.96s\n```",
